text.tspan: - A rich multi-user web-based tool for linguistic annotation of documents; fully open source
- Powered by the FoLiA format, unlocking a rich infrastructure of tools
- Supports a wide variety of linguistic annotation types
- Retains and visualises document structure; annotation on multiple levels
Local annotations: Hover over words to display detailed linguistic annotations
Click words to open the annotation editor
Selection fields are populated by FoLiA Set Definitions referenced from the document,
neither FLAT nor FoLiA predefine values, you can define your own!

Visualisation of syntax and morphology trees
In-document search using CQL or FoLiA Query Language (FQL). All actions in
editor are expressed as FQL queries and send to the backend document server.

- Annotator name and timestamps are stored with every
